cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.AL, cs.IT, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with a problem in data structures (reordering buffer problem) and provides a lower bound on the performance of an offline algorithm, which suggests that the problem is difficult to solve optimally. This makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) the most likely category. The paper also involves game theory (competitive analysis), which makes cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) another likely category. The paper uses techniques from approximation algorithms (offline algorithm with buffer k vs (1-delta) k), which makes cs.AL (Computational Complexity and Approximation Algorithms) another possible category. The paper also involves information theory (logarithmic factor) and machine learning (optimization), which makes cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) possible categories as well.
